<glossary>
<definition id="geodist">
    <term>geometric distribution</term>
    <meaning id="id14905098">a discrete random variable (RV) that arises from the Bernoulli trials; the trials are repeated until the first success.
<newline/>The geometric variable <emphasis effect="italics">X</emphasis> is defined as the number of trials until the first success. Notation <emphasis effect="italics">X</emphasis> ~ <emphasis effect="italics">G</emphasis>(<emphasis effect="italics">p</emphasis>). The mean is <emphasis effect="italics">μ</emphasis> = <m:math>
 <m:mrow>
  <m:mfrac>
   <m:mn>1</m:mn>
   <m:mi>p</m:mi>
  </m:mfrac>
 </m:mrow>
</m:math> and the standard deviation is <emphasis effect="italics">σ</emphasis> = <m:math>
 <m:mrow>
  <m:msqrt>
   <m:mrow>
    <m:mfrac>
     <m:mn>1</m:mn>
     <m:mi>p</m:mi>
    </m:mfrac>
    <m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo>
     <m:mrow>
      <m:mfrac>
       <m:mn>1</m:mn>
       <m:mi>p</m:mi>
      </m:mfrac>
      <m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn>
     </m:mrow>
    <m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow>
   </m:mrow>
  </m:msqrt>

 </m:mrow>
</m:math>. The probability of exactly <emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis> failures before the first success is given by the formula <equation class="unnumbered" id="fs-idm257614544"><label/><m:math><m:mi>P</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>X</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>p</m:mi><m:msup><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>–</m:mo><m:mi>p</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>–</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:math></equation>.</meaning>
  </definition>

<definition id="fs-idm64151840">
<term>geometric experiment</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm13336304">a statistical experiment with the following properties:
<list id="fs-idm65008928" list-type="enumerated">
<item>There are one or more Bernoulli trials with all failures except the last one, which is a success</item>
